    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "4e2f137c_abe4b9a7",
        "filename": "tests/SkSLMetalTest.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 4
      },
      "lineNbr": 102,
      "author": {
        "id": 11059
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-05-28T16:20:40Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This looks like a strange quirk of constant propagation, although I haven\u0027t investigated it too deeply. I wrote some unit tests which confirm this behavior though:\n\n- If the original float2x2 is constructed via \"float2x2(float4(1,2,3,4))\" it will generate the helper.\n- If the original float2x2 is constructed via \"float2x2(float2(1,2),float2(3,4))\" it will not need a helper.\n\nThis seems worthy of investigation at some point since it seems like constant propagation might be leaking type information in some subtle way.",
      "parentUuid": "65a44a6a_418434cb",
